Class JvmNestedClass

java.lang.Object
me.sbasalaev.tybyco.descriptors.JvmClass
me.sbasalaev.tybyco.descriptors.JvmNestedClass
All Implemented Interfaces:
JvmClassOrArray
public final class JvmNestedClass extends JvmClass
Name and attributes for a nested, member, local or anonymous class. Nested classes are treated specially in two contexts of the classfile. First, the signature of a member class includes the signature of its enclosing class. Second, the classfile stores simple names and attributes of all the nested classes it references in the InnerClasses attribute. To automate the generation of the corresponding attributes all the information is gathered in this class.

To make a reference for a nested class first make a reference to its enclosing class and then call the appropriate newMember(), newLocal() or newAnonymous().

See Also:
  • JVMS 4.7.6 The InnerClasses Attribute
